The paper deals with video co-segmentation, which is a task in computer vision. The paper also mentions subspace clustering, which is a common technique in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions a novel framework based on the self-expressiveness model, which is a machine learning technique, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also deals with motion features, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also mentions the use of affine subspaces, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with improving the robustness of the algorithm, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
